## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook case of **"coverage without verification"** — every production method is exercised (achieving line coverage) but almost nothing is actually asserted. These tests cannot catch regressions.

---

### Severity-Ranked Findings

#### 🔴 CRITICAL — Assertion-Free Tests (no verification at all)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | Calls `AddProduct` then asserts **nothing**. Cannot detect if save silently fails. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-36) | Calls `UpdatePrice` then never checks the product's price changed. A no-op implementation passes. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39-43) | Removes a product but never verifies it's actually gone. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | Doesn't even assert the count equals 0. Literally dead code. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | Applies a 10% discount to two products but never checks any price decreased. **This is the highest-risk gap** — bulk discount logic has subtle math (`Price * (1 - fraction)`) that goes completely unverified. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85-88) | Imports data but never verifies any product was created or parsed correctly. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Example: ApplyBulkDiscount
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesCorrectly()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 100.00m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
    var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(90.00m, result!.Price);
}
```

---

#### 🟠 HIGH — Shallow/Trivial Assertions (`IsNotNull` on non-nullable paths)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L25-29) | Asserts `IsNotNull` but never checks that `result.Sku`, `Name`, or `Price` match. A store returning *any* product passes. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L47-52) | Asserts `IsNotNull` on the list but never checks `Count == 1` or that "Widget" was found (not "Gadget"). |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Same — `IsNotNull` on list, never checks it contains the added product or has count 1. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77-82) | `IsNotNull` on the CSV string — never checks content matches `"SKU-001,Widget,9.99"`. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Example: SearchProducts
[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsOnlyMatchingProducts()
{
